This paper discusses the optimization of job assignment and replication in cloud computing systems, which involves distributed computing, system design, and network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also analyzes the impact of different replication strategies on latency and cost, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also discusses the trade-off between latency and cost, which involves system optimization and control theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also discusses the impact of network variability on latency, which involves network infrastructure and protocols, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of service time distribution on replication strategies, which involves probability and statistics, making cs.PF (Probability) a possible category.
